  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.bs.dto.IDto<IReceivable>, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.bs.dto.IDto<IReceivable>>

    public class BsReceivable
extends AbstractBsReceivable

    A business layer data-transfer object for the Receivable. This class is the concrete subclass of the generated abstract class. Make any changes to DTO behavior by overriding methods here rather than changing the abstract superclass; AndroMDA will overwrite that class when you run it but will never overwrite this concrete subclass.

        Create a BsReceivable. This constructor calls the abstract superclass constructor.

        Parameters:
        key - the primary key of the Receivable
        orderNumber - composite sub-key attribute and order number within transaction
        transactionId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        amount - the monetary amount in dollars of the transaction item
        debit - whether the item is a debit (true) or credit (false); default value is the debit-default value of the account
        checked - whether the value and details of the transaction item have been verified and reconciled
        accountName - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
        entityName - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
